I went to eat at this location with my family and ended up having a not so good of an experience. The two guys working there spent more time looking at their laptop than the actual customers, they didn't even check on us after we got our food. When it comes to the food it as good as the main location the only thing I noticed the food portions are a lot smaller than the original location. The inside of the  restaurant looks nice its not big but not small either. Be ready to pay for street parking, the location has big glass windows so if you're lucky you'll get a spot right infront so you dont have to pay parking but be on the  look out for the ticket personel. At the end we had finished our delitious food and I was expecting the waiter to check if we needed anything unfortunately it didn't happen, so I had to signal one of the guys to come to our table so we could get the check also another group of people had to do the same to get their attention because they needed something (I dont know what) for their food. I won't come back here to dine in (unless I have no ther choice) I would order take out from this location only  but for that I'll order at the main location.
